            <thetext>qooxdoos property system creates the accessor methods automatically for properties. If a property is faked by hand written accessors, e.g. for deprecation, information will be lost like the check, the event. The code itself like the check can be implemented in the hand written function but the information can not be read by other code parts like the data binding or the inspector.

Perhaps a solution is to ad annotation to the hand written setter and attach the check information here. That information could be accessed by the data binding code and could act like its accessing a property.</thetext>
